            <commentid>27535</commentid>
            <who name="Daniel Wagner">daniel.wagner</who>
            <bug_when>2011-11-15 10:41:45 +0100</bug_when>
            <thetext>Lint will report the top-level namespace of any library included in the current application as an unidentified global, e.g. qxc in most of the demo apps. The Generator should add these namespaces to the list of known globals before the lint scan is started.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
          <long_desc isprivate="0">
            <commentid>30460</commentid>
            <who name="Thomas Herchenroeder">thron7</who>
            <bug_when>2012-08-22 17:02:39 +0200</bug_when>
            <thetext>With the new lint module the generator&#39;s &#39;lint&#39; job now honors the &#39;libraries&#39; 
key, so you can pass the same libraries as with the compile jobs. The net 
result is that not only namespaces of used libraries are recognized, but exact 
class names are checked (so e.g. an incorrect class name from a used library 
will be warned about as unknown).</thetext>
          </long_desc>
